# Müxtəlif ssenariləri üçün test məlumatları yaradaq
set.seed(2025)

# Scenario 1: İdeal IRT data (bütün fərziyyələr təmin olunur)
create_ideal_irt_data <- function(n_persons = 500, n_items = 15) {
  theta <- rnorm(n_persons, 0, 1)
  
  # Item parameters
  discrimination <- runif(n_items, 0.8, 2.2)
  difficulty <- seq(-2, 2, length.out = n_items)
  
  # Generate responses
  data <- matrix(NA, n_persons, n_items)
  for(i in 1:n_persons) {
    for(j in 1:n_items) {
      prob <- calculate_icc_2pl(theta[i], discrimination[j], difficulty[j])
      data[i, j] <- rbinom(1, 1, prob)
    }
  }
  
  colnames(data) <- paste0("Item", 1:n_items)
  return(list(data = data, theta = theta, 
              discrimination = discrimination, difficulty = difficulty))
}

# Scenario 2: Multidimensional data (Unidimensionality pozulması)
create_multidim_data <- function(n_persons = 500, n_items = 15) {
  # İki faktorial struktur
  theta1 <- rnorm(n_persons, 0, 1)  # Verbal
  theta2 <- rnorm(n_persons, 0, 1)  # Quantitative
  
  discrimination <- runif(n_items, 0.8, 2.2)
  difficulty <- seq(-2, 2, length.out = n_items)
  
  data <- matrix(NA, n_persons, n_items)
  for(i in 1:n_persons) {
    for(j in 1:n_items) {
      if(j <= n_items/2) {
        # Verbal items
        prob <- calculate_icc_2pl(theta1[i], discrimination[j], difficulty[j])
      } else {
        # Quantitative items
        prob <- calculate_icc_2pl(theta2[i], discrimination[j], difficulty[j])
      }
      data[i, j] <- rbinom(1, 1, prob)
    }
  }
  
  colnames(data) <- paste0("Item", 1:n_items)
  return(list(data = data, theta1 = theta1, theta2 = theta2,
              discrimination = discrimination, difficulty = difficulty))
}

# Scenario 3: Local dependence (chaining effect)
create_localdep_data <- function(n_persons = 500, n_items = 15) {
  theta <- rnorm(n_persons, 0, 1)
  
  discrimination <- runif(n_items, 0.8, 2.2)
  difficulty <- seq(-2, 2, length.out = n_items)
  
  data <- matrix(NA, n_persons, n_items)
  
  for(i in 1:n_persons) {
    for(j in 1:n_items) {
      prob <- calculate_icc_2pl(theta[i], discrimination[j], difficulty[j])
      
      # Local dependence: Items 5-6 və 10-11 arasında
      if(j == 6 && !is.na(data[i, 5]) && data[i, 5] == 1) {
        prob <- min(0.95, prob * 1.8)  # Boost if item 5 correct
      }
      if(j == 11 && !is.na(data[i, 10]) && data[i, 10] == 1) {
        prob <- min(0.95, prob * 1.8)  # Boost if item 10 correct
      }
      
      data[i, j] <- rbinom(1, 1, prob)
    }
  }
  
  colnames(data) <- paste0("Item", 1:n_items)
  return(list(data = data, theta = theta,
              discrimination = discrimination, difficulty = difficulty))
}

3 Unidimensionality Testing (Ətraflı)

3.1 Factor Analysis Metodları

cat("=== UNİDİMENSİONALİTY TESİNG (ƏTRAFLII) ===\n\n")
## === UNİDİMENSİONALİTY TESİNG (ƏTRAFLII) ===
# Factor analysis funksiyası
perform_dimensionality_analysis <- function(data, data_name) {
  cat("=== ", toupper(data_name), " DATA ANALİZİ ===\n")
  
  tryCatch({
    # 1. Correlation matrix
    cor_matrix <- cor(data, use = "complete.obs")
    
    # 2. Eigenvalue analysis
    eigenvals <- eigen(cor_matrix)$values
    
    cat("Eigenvalue Statistikaları:\n")
    for(i in 1:min(5, length(eigenvals))) {
      cat(sprintf("  λ%d = %.3f (%.1f%%)\n", i, eigenvals[i], 
                  100 * eigenvals[i] / sum(eigenvals)))
    }
    
    # 3. Unidimensionality kriterləri
    lambda_ratio <- eigenvals[1] / eigenvals[2]
    first_factor_var <- 100 * eigenvals[1] / sum(eigenvals)
    
    cat("\nUnidimensionality Kriterləri:\n")
    cat("  λ₁/λ₂ ratio:", round(lambda_ratio, 2), "\n")
    cat("  Birinci faktor variansı:", round(first_factor_var, 1), "%\n")
    
    # Qiymətləndirmə
    if(lambda_ratio > 3 && first_factor_var > 40) {
      assessment <- "Güclü unidimensional"
    } else if(lambda_ratio > 2 && first_factor_var > 30) {
      assessment <- "Zəif unidimensional"  
    } else if(lambda_ratio > 1.5 && first_factor_var > 25) {
      assessment <- "Şübhəli unidimensional"
    } else {
      assessment <- "Multidimensional"
    }
    
    cat("  Qiymətləndirmə:", assessment, "\n\n")
    
    # 4. Scree plot
    if(require(ggplot2, quietly = TRUE)) {
      scree_data <- data.frame(
        Factor = 1:min(10, length(eigenvals)),
        Eigenvalue = eigenvals[1:min(10, length(eigenvals))]
      )
      
      scree_plot <- ggplot(scree_data, aes(x = Factor, y = Eigenvalue)) +
        geom_line(color = "blue", size = 1) +
        geom_point(color = "red", size = 3) +
        geom_hline(yintercept = 1, linetype = "dashed", color = "gray") +
        labs(title = paste("Scree Plot -", data_name),
             x = "Factor Number", y = "Eigenvalue") +
        theme_minimal() +
        scale_x_continuous(breaks = 1:min(10, length(eigenvals)))
      
      print(scree_plot)
    }
    
    # 5. Factor analysis (if psych available)
    if(require(psych, quietly = TRUE)) {
      fa_result <- tryCatch({
        fa(data, nfactors = 2, rotate = "varimax", fm = "ml")
      }, error = function(e) {
        fa(cor_matrix, nfactors = 2, rotate = "varimax", fm = "ml")
      })
      
      cat("Factor Analysis Nəticələri:\n")
      cat("  Factor 1 loadings aralığı:", 
          round(min(fa_result$loadings[,1]), 3), "-", 
          round(max(fa_result$loadings[,1]), 3), "\n")
      
      if(ncol(fa_result$loadings) > 1) {
        cat("  Factor 2 loadings aralığı:", 
            round(min(fa_result$loadings[,2]), 3), "-", 
            round(max(fa_result$loadings[,2]), 3), "\n")
      }
      
      # Cross-loadings detection
      if(ncol(fa_result$loadings) > 1) {
        high_cross_loadings <- sum(abs(fa_result$loadings[,2]) > 0.30)
        cat("  Yüksək cross-loading sayı (>0.30):", high_cross_loadings, "\n")
      }
      
      cat("  RMSEA:", round(fa_result$RMSEA[1], 3), "\n")
      cat("  TLI:", round(fa_result$TLI, 3), "\n\n")
    }
    
    return(list(eigenvals = eigenvals, lambda_ratio = lambda_ratio, 
                first_factor_var = first_factor_var, assessment = assessment))
    
  }, error = function(e) {
    cat("Factor analysis xətası:", e$message, "\n\n")
    return(NULL)
  })
}

# Bütün ssenariləri analiz et

for(i in 1:length(scenarios)) {
  dim_results[[names(scenarios)[i]]] <- 
    perform_dimensionality_analysis(scenarios[[i]], names(scenarios)[i])

3.2 Parallel Analysis

cat("\n=== PARALLEL ANALİZ ===\n\n")

## === PARALLEL ANALİZ ===
# Parallel analysis funksiyası
perform_parallel_analysis <- function(data, data_name, n_iterations = 100) {
  cat("Parallel Analysis:", data_name, "\n")
  
  n_obs <- nrow(data)
  n_vars <- ncol(data)
  
  # Observed eigenvalues
  obs_eigenvals <- eigen(cor(data, use = "complete.obs"))$values
  
  # Random eigenvalues
  random_eigenvals <- matrix(NA, n_iterations, n_vars)
  
  for(i in 1:n_iterations) {
    random_data <- matrix(rnorm(n_obs * n_vars), n_obs, n_vars)
    random_eigenvals[i, ] <- eigen(cor(random_data))$values
  }
  
  # 95th percentile of random eigenvalues
  random_eigenvals_95 <- apply(random_eigenvals, 2, quantile, 0.95)
  
  # Number of factors to retain
  factors_to_retain <- sum(obs_eigenvals > random_eigenvals_95)
  
  cat("  Tövsiyə olunan faktorial sayı:", factors_to_retain, "\n")
  
  # Plot comparison
  if(require(ggplot2, quietly = TRUE)) {
    factor_nums <- 1:min(8, n_vars)
    pa_data <- data.frame(
      Factor = factor_nums,
      Observed = obs_eigenvals[factor_nums],
      Random_95th = random_eigenvals_95[factor_nums]
    )
    
    pa_plot <- ggplot(pa_data) +
      geom_line(aes(x = Factor, y = Observed, color = "Observed"), size = 1.2) +
      geom_line(aes(x = Factor, y = Random_95th, color = "Random 95th"), size = 1.2) +
      geom_point(aes(x = Factor, y = Observed, color = "Observed"), size = 3) +
      geom_point(aes(x = Factor, y = Random_95th, color = "Random 95th"), size = 3) +
      scale_color_manual(values = c("Observed" = "blue", "Random 95th" = "red")) +
      labs(title = paste("Parallel Analysis -", data_name),
           x = "Factor Number", y = "Eigenvalue",
           color = "Data Type") +
      theme_minimal()
    
    print(pa_plot)
  }
  
  cat("  Observed eigenvalues > Random 95th:\n")
  for(i in 1:min(5, length(obs_eigenvals))) {
    exceed <- obs_eigenvals[i] > random_eigenvals_95[i]
    status <- ifelse(exceed, "✓", "✗")
    cat(sprintf("    Factor %d: %.3f vs %.3f %s\n", 
                i, obs_eigenvals[i], random_eigenvals_95[i], status))
  }
  cat("\n")
  
  return(factors_to_retain)
}

# Parallel analysis bütün ssenariləri üçün

  pa_results[[names(scenarios)[i]]] <- 
    perform_parallel_analysis(scenarios[[i]], names(scenarios)[i])

4 Local Independence Testing

4.1 Q3 Statistikası və Residual Correlations

cat("\n=== LOCAL INDEPENDENCE TESİNG ===\n\n")
## 
## === LOCAL INDEPENDENCE TESİNG ===
# Q3 statistikası hesablama funksiyası
calculate_q3_matrix <- function(data, theta_estimates = NULL) {
  
  # Əgər theta estimates verilməyibsə, total score istifadə et
  if(is.null(theta_estimates)) {
    total_scores <- rowSums(data, na.rm = TRUE)
    theta_estimates <- scale(total_scores)[, 1]
  }
  
  n_items <- ncol(data)
  n_persons <- nrow(data)
  
  # Expected response probabilities (simplified 2PL approximation)
  expected_probs <- matrix(NA, n_persons, n_items)
  
  for(j in 1:n_items) {
    # Simplified item parameters estimation
    item_mean <- mean(data[, j], na.rm = TRUE)
    item_difficulty <- qlogis(item_mean)  # Approximate difficulty
    
    for(i in 1:n_persons) {
      expected_probs[i, j] <- plogis(theta_estimates[i] - item_difficulty)
    }
  }
  
  # Residuals
  residuals <- data - expected_probs
  
  # Residual correlation matrix (Q3)
  q3_matrix <- cor(residuals, use = "complete.obs")
  diag(q3_matrix) <- NA
  
  return(q3_matrix)
}

# Q3 analysis for all scenarios
perform_q3_analysis <- function(data, data_name) {
  cat("=== Q3 ANALİZİ:", toupper(data_name), "===\n")
  
  q3_matrix <- calculate_q3_matrix(data)
  
  # Q3 statistikaları
  q3_values <- q3_matrix[!is.na(q3_matrix)]
  
  cat("Q3 Statistikaları:\n")
  cat("  Orta Q3:", round(mean(q3_values), 3), "\n")
  cat("  SD Q3:", round(sd(q3_values), 3), "\n")
  cat("  Min Q3:", round(min(q3_values), 3), "\n")
  cat("  Max Q3:", round(max(q3_values), 3), "\n")
  
  # Threshold violations
  high_q3_pairs <- sum(q3_values > 0.20, na.rm = TRUE)
  very_high_q3_pairs <- sum(q3_values > 0.30, na.rm = TRUE)
  
  cat("  Q3 > 0.20 (şübhəli LD):", high_q3_pairs, "pair\n")
  cat("  Q3 > 0.30 (güclü LD):", very_high_q3_pairs, "pair\n")
  
  # Overall assessment
  if(very_high_q3_pairs > 0) {
    ld_assessment <- "Güclü Local Dependence"
  } else if(high_q3_pairs > 2) {
    ld_assessment <- "Orta Local Dependence"
  } else if(high_q3_pairs > 0) {
    ld_assessment <- "Zəif Local Dependence"
  } else {
    ld_assessment <- "Local Independence"
  }
  
  cat("  Qiymətləndirmə:", ld_assessment, "\n\n")
  
  # Ən yüksək Q3 dəyərləri
  if(high_q3_pairs > 0) {
    # Find pairs with highest Q3
    q3_upper <- q3_matrix
    q3_upper[lower.tri(q3_upper, diag = TRUE)] <- NA
    
    # Top problematic pairs
    high_indices <- which(q3_upper > 0.20, arr.ind = TRUE)
    if(nrow(high_indices) > 0) {
      cat("Ən Problematik Item Pairs (Q3 > 0.20):\n")
      for(i in 1:min(5, nrow(high_indices))) {
        row_idx <- high_indices[i, 1]
        col_idx <- high_indices[i, 2]
        q3_val <- q3_matrix[row_idx, col_idx]
        cat(sprintf("  Item %d - Item %d: Q3 = %.3f\n", 
                    row_idx, col_idx, q3_val))
      }
      cat("\n")
    }
  }
  
  # Q3 heatmap (if corrplot available)
  if(require(corrplot, quietly = TRUE) && ncol(data) <= 20) {
    tryCatch({
      corrplot(q3_matrix, method = "color", type = "upper",
               title = paste("Q3 Matrix -", data_name),
               tl.cex = 0.8, tl.col = "black",
               mar = c(0,0,2,0))
    }, error = function(e) {
      cat("Q3 heatmap çəkilə bilmədi\n")
    })
  }
  
  return(list(q3_matrix = q3_matrix, q3_values = q3_values, 
              assessment = ld_assessment, high_pairs = high_q3_pairs))
}

5 Monotonicity Checking: Mokken Scale Analysis

5.1 Mokken Model və Loevinger H Coefficients

cat("\n=== MONOTONİCİTY CHECKİNG: MOKKEN SCALE ANALİZİ ===\n\n")
## 
## === MONOTONİCİTY CHECKİNG: MOKKEN SCALE ANALİZİ ===
# Mokken analysis funksiyası
perform_mokken_analysis <- function(data, data_name) {
  cat("=== MOKKEN ANALİZİ:", toupper(data_name), "===\n")
  
  if(!require(mokken, quietly = TRUE)) {
    cat("mokken paketi mövcud deyil. Manual monotonicity check aparılır.\n\n")
    return(perform_manual_monotonicity_check(data, data_name))
  }
  
  tryCatch({
    # 1. Scalability coefficients
    scale_coefs <- coefH(data)
    
    cat("Scalability Coefficients (Loevinger H):\n")
    cat("  Total scale H:", round(scale_coefs$H, 3), "\n")
    
    # Item-level H coefficients
    if(!is.null(scale_coefs$Hi)) {
      cat("  Item H coefficients:\n")
      for(i in 1:length(scale_coefs$Hi)) {
        quality <- ifelse(scale_coefs$Hi[i] >= 0.50, "Güclü",
                         ifelse(scale_coefs$Hi[i] >= 0.40, "Orta",
                               ifelse(scale_coefs$Hi[i] >= 0.30, "Zəif", "Problemli")))
        cat(sprintf("    Item %d: H = %.3f (%s)\n", 
                    i, scale_coefs$Hi[i], quality))
      }
    }
    
    # Pair-wise H coefficients
    if(!is.null(scale_coefs$Hij)) {
      hij_values <- scale_coefs$Hij[upper.tri(scale_coefs$Hij)]
      cat("  Pair-wise H statistikaları:\n")
      cat("    Orta Hij:", round(mean(hij_values, na.rm = TRUE), 3), "\n")
      cat("    Min Hij:", round(min(hij_values, na.rm = TRUE), 3), "\n")
      
      negative_pairs <- sum(hij_values < 0, na.rm = TRUE)
      cat("    Mənfi Hij pair sayı:", negative_pairs, "\n")
    }
    
    # 2. Monotonicity check
    cat("\nMonotonicity Check:\n")
    mono_check <- check.monotonicity(data)
    
    # Summary of violations
    if(!is.null(mono_check$summary)) {
      violations <- mono_check$summary
      total_violations <- sum(violations, na.rm = TRUE)
      cat("  Monotonicity violations:", total_violations, "\n")
      
      if(total_violations > 0) {
        cat("  Problematik itemlər:\n")
        problematic_items <- which(violations > 0)
        for(item in problematic_items) {
          cat(sprintf("    Item %d: %d pozulma\n", item, violations[item]))
        }
      }
    }
    
    # 3. IIO (Invariant Item Ordering) check
    cat("\nInvariant Item Ordering Check:\n")
    iio_check <- check.iio(data)
    
    if(!is.null(iio_check$HT)) {
      iio_violations <- sum(iio_check$HT < 0.05, na.rm = TRUE)
      cat("  IIO violations (p < 0.05):", iio_violations, "\n")
    }
    
    # 4. Overall Mokken scale quality
    total_h <- scale_coefs$H
    if(total_h >= 0.50) {
      mokken_quality <- "Güclü Mokken Scale"
    } else if(total_h >= 0.40) {
      mokken_quality <- "Orta Mokken Scale"
    } else if(total_h >= 0.30) {
      mokken_quality <- "Zəif Mokken Scale"
    } else {
      mokken_quality <- "Mokken Scale Deyil"
    }
    
    cat("\nÜmumi Qiymətləndirmə:", mokken_quality, "\n\n")
    
    return(list(H = scale_coefs$H, Hi = scale_coefs$Hi,
                mono_violations = total_violations,
                quality = mokken_quality))
    
  }, error = function(e) {
    cat("Mokken analysis xətası:", e$message, "\n")
    cat("Manual check aparılır...\n\n")
    return(perform_manual_monotonicity_check(data, data_name))
  })
}

# Manual monotonicity check (mokken paketi olmayanda)
perform_manual_monotonicity_check <- function(data, data_name) {
  cat("=== MANUAL MONOTONİCİTY CHECK:", toupper(data_name), "===\n")
  
  # Total score grouplarına görə item means
  total_scores <- rowSums(data, na.rm = TRUE)
  n_groups <- 5  # Quantile groups
  
  # Create score groups
  score_groups <- cut(total_scores, 
                     breaks = quantile(total_scores, seq(0, 1, length.out = n_groups + 1)),
                     include.lowest = TRUE, labels = FALSE)
  
  # Check monotonicity for each item
  monotonicity_violations <- 0
  
  cat("Item Monotonicity Check (by score groups):\n")
  for(j in 1:ncol(data)) {
    group_means <- tapply(data[, j], score_groups, mean, na.rm = TRUE)
    
    # Check if means are increasing
    is_monotonic <- all(diff(group_means) >= -0.05, na.rm = TRUE)  # Allow small deviations
    
    if(!is_monotonic) {
      monotonicity_violations <- monotonicity_violations + 1
      cat(sprintf("  Item %d: NON-MONOTONIC (means: %s)\n", 
                  j, paste(round(group_means, 3), collapse = ", ")))
    } else {
      cat(sprintf("  Item %d: Monotonic ✓\n", j))
    }
  }
  
  cat("\nMonotonicity violations:", monotonicity_violations, "/", ncol(data), "\n")
  
  if(monotonicity_violations == 0) {
    mono_quality <- "Monotonic"
  } else if(monotonicity_violations <= ncol(data) * 0.2) {
    mono_quality <- "Mostly Monotonic"
  } else {
    mono_quality <- "Non-Monotonic"
  }
  
  cat("Qiymətləndirmə:", mono_quality, "\n\n")
  
  return(list(violations = monotonicity_violations, quality = mono_quality))
}

6 Model Fit Assessment

6.1 Fit Indices və Goodness of Fit Tests

cat("\n=== MODEL FİT ASSESSMENT ===\n\n")
## 
## === MODEL FİT ASSESSMENT ===
# IRT model fit analysis funksiyası
perform_irt_fit_analysis <- function(data, data_name) {
  cat("=== IRT MODEL FİT:", toupper(data_name), "===\n")
  
  # ltm paketi ilə model fit
  if(require(ltm, quietly = TRUE)) {
    tryCatch({
      # Fit 1PL ve 2PL models
      cat("1PL (Rasch) Model Fitting...\n")
      model_1pl <- rasch(data, constraint = cbind(1:ncol(data), 1))
      
      cat("2PL Model Fitting...\n") 
      model_2pl <- ltm(data ~ z1)
      
      # Model comparison
      aic_1pl <- AIC(model_1pl)
      aic_2pl <- AIC(model_2pl)
      bic_1pl <- BIC(model_1pl)
      bic_2pl <- BIC(model_2pl)
      
      loglik_1pl <- logLik(model_1pl)
      loglik_2pl <- logLik(model_2pl)
      
      cat("\nModel Comparison:\n")
      cat("1PL Model:\n")
      cat("  AIC:", round(aic_1pl, 2), "\n")
      cat("  BIC:", round(bic_1pl, 2), "\n")
      cat("  Log-Likelihood:", round(as.numeric(loglik_1pl), 2), "\n")
      
      cat("2PL Model:\n")
      cat("  AIC:", round(aic_2pl, 2), "\n")
      cat("  BIC:", round(bic_2pl, 2), "\n")
      cat("  Log-Likelihood:", round(as.numeric(loglik_2pl), 2), "\n")
      
      # Likelihood ratio test
      lr_statistic <- 2 * (as.numeric(loglik_2pl) - as.numeric(loglik_1pl))
      df_diff <- attr(loglik_2pl, "df") - attr(loglik_1pl, "df")
      lr_p_value <- 1 - pchisq(lr_statistic, df_diff)
      
      cat("\nLikelihood Ratio Test (2PL vs 1PL):\n")
      cat("  LR Statistic:", round(lr_statistic, 2), "\n")
      cat("  df:", df_diff, "\n")
      cat("  p-value:", ifelse(lr_p_value < 0.001, "<0.001", round(lr_p_value, 3)), "\n")
      
      if(lr_p_value < 0.05) {
        cat("  → 2PL model əhəmiyyətli dərəcədə yaxşıdır\n")
        preferred_model <- model_2pl
        preferred_name <- "2PL"
      } else {
        cat("  → 1PL model kifayətdir\n") 
        preferred_model <- model_1pl
        preferred_name <- "1PL"
      }
      
      # Item fit statistics (for preferred model)
      cat("\nItem Fit Statistics (", preferred_name, "model):\n")
      
      # Person fit
      cat("\nPerson Fit Statistics:\n")
      person_fit <- person.fit(preferred_model)
      
      if(!is.null(person_fit)) {
        # Misfitting persons
        misfit_persons <- sum(person_fit$p.values < 0.05, na.rm = TRUE)
        total_persons <- length(person_fit$p.values)
        misfit_rate <- 100 * misfit_persons / total_persons
        
        cat("  Misfitting persons (p < 0.05):", misfit_persons, "/", total_persons,
            "(", round(misfit_rate, 1), "%)\n")
        
        if(misfit_rate < 5) {
          person_fit_quality <- "Yaxşı"
        } else if(misfit_rate < 10) {
          person_fit_quality <- "Məqbul"
        } else {
          person_fit_quality <- "Problemli"
        }
        
        cat("  Person fit keyfiyyəti:", person_fit_quality, "\n")
      }
      
      cat("\n")
      
      return(list(
        aic_1pl = aic_1pl, aic_2pl = aic_2pl,
        bic_1pl = bic_1pl, bic_2pl = bic_2pl,
        lr_statistic = lr_statistic, lr_p_value = lr_p_value,
        preferred_model = preferred_name,
        misfit_rate = ifelse(exists("misfit_rate"), misfit_rate, NA),
        person_fit_quality = ifelse(exists("person_fit_quality"), person_fit_quality, "N/A")
      ))
      
    }, error = function(e) {
      cat("ltm model fit xətası:", e$message, "\n\n")
      return(perform_manual_fit_assessment(data, data_name))
    })
    
  } else {
    cat("ltm paketi mövcud deyil. Manual fit assessment aparılır.\n")
    return(perform_manual_fit_assessment(data, data_name))
  }
}

# Manual fit assessment (ltm olmayanda)
perform_manual_fit_assessment <- function(data, data_name) {
  cat("=== MANUAL FİT ASSESSMENT:", toupper(data_name), "===\n")
  
  # Basic CTT statistics as proxy for fit
  total_scores <- rowSums(data, na.rm = TRUE)
  
  # Internal consistency
  if(require(psych, quietly = TRUE)) {
    alpha_result <- alpha(data, check.keys = FALSE)
    cronbach_alpha <- alpha_result$total$std.alpha
    
    cat("Cronbach's Alpha:", round(cronbach_alpha, 3), "\n")
    
    # Item-total correlations
    item_total_cors <- alpha_result$item.stats$r.cor
    low_discrimination <- sum(item_total_cors < 0.20, na.rm = TRUE)
    
    cat("Aşağı diskriminasiya itemləri (r < 0.20):", low_discrimination, "\n")
  }
  
  # Score distribution
  cat("Score distribution:\n")
  cat("  Min:", min(total_scores), "\n")
  cat("  Max:", max(total_scores), "\n")
  cat("  Mean:", round(mean(total_scores), 2), "\n")
  cat("  SD:", round(sd(total_scores), 2), "\n")
  
  # Floor və ceiling effects
  max_possible <- ncol(data)
  floor_effect <- 100 * sum(total_scores == 0) / length(total_scores)
  ceiling_effect <- 100 * sum(total_scores == max_possible) / length(total_scores)
  
  cat("  Floor effect:", round(floor_effect, 1), "%\n")
  cat("  Ceiling effect:", round(ceiling_effect, 1), "%\n")
  
  # Overall assessment
  if(exists("cronbach_alpha") && cronbach_alpha > 0.80 && 
     floor_effect < 5 && ceiling_effect < 5) {
    fit_quality <- "Yaxşı"
  } else if(exists("cronbach_alpha") && cronbach_alpha > 0.70) {
    fit_quality <- "Məqbul"  
  } else {
    fit_quality <- "Problemli"
  }
  
  cat("Manual fit qiymətləndirməsi:", fit_quality, "\n\n")
  
  return(list(
    alpha = ifelse(exists("cronbach_alpha"), cronbach_alpha, NA),
    floor_effect = floor_effect,
    ceiling_effect = ceiling_effect,
    fit_quality = fit_quality
  ))
}

}

7 Residual Analysis

7.1 Standardized Residuals və Diagnostic Plots

cat("\n=== RESİDUAL ANALİZİ ===\n\n")
## 
## === RESİDUAL ANALİZİ ===
# Residual analysis funksiyası
perform_residual_analysis <- function(data, data_name) {
  cat("=== RESİDUAL ANALİZ:", toupper(data_name), "===\n")
  
  # Simple theta estimation using total scores
  total_scores <- rowSums(data, na.rm = TRUE)
  theta_est <- scale(total_scores)[, 1]
  
  # Expected probabilities (simplified 2PL)
  n_persons <- nrow(data)
  n_items <- ncol(data)
  expected_probs <- matrix(NA, n_persons, n_items)
  
  for(j in 1:n_items) {
    # Simplified item parameter estimation
    item_mean <- mean(data[, j], na.rm = TRUE)
    item_difficulty <- qlogis(item_mean)
    
    # Assume discrimination = 1 for simplicity
    discrimination <- 1
    
    for(i in 1:n_persons) {
      expected_probs[i, j] <- plogis(discrimination * (theta_est[i] - item_difficulty))
    }
  }
  
  # Raw residuals
  raw_residuals <- data - expected_probs
  
  # Standardized residuals
  residual_variances <- expected_probs * (1 - expected_probs)
  std_residuals <- raw_residuals / sqrt(residual_variances)
  
  # Residual statistics
  cat("Residual Statistikaları:\n")
  cat("  Raw residuals:\n")
  cat("    Mean:", round(mean(raw_residuals, na.rm = TRUE), 4), "\n")
  cat("    SD:", round(sd(raw_residuals, na.rm = TRUE), 3), "\n")
  cat("    Min:", round(min(raw_residuals, na.rm = TRUE), 3), "\n") 
  cat("    Max:", round(max(raw_residuals, na.rm = TRUE), 3), "\n")
  
  cat("  Standardized residuals:\n")
  cat("    Mean:", round(mean(std_residuals, na.rm = TRUE), 4), "\n")
  cat("    SD:", round(sd(std_residuals, na.rm = TRUE), 3), "\n")
  cat("    Min:", round(min(std_residuals, na.rm = TRUE), 3), "\n")
  cat("    Max:", round(max(std_residuals, na.rm = TRUE), 3), "\n")
  
  # Outlier detection
  outlier_threshold <- 2.5
  outliers <- abs(std_residuals) > outlier_threshold
  n_outliers <- sum(outliers, na.rm = TRUE)
  total_responses <- sum(!is.na(std_residuals))
  outlier_rate <- 100 * n_outliers / total_responses
  
  cat("  Outliers (|z| > 2.5):", n_outliers, "/", total_responses, 
      "(", round(outlier_rate, 1), "%)\n")
  
  # Item-level residual analysis
  cat("\nItem-Level Residual Analysis:\n")
  for(j in 1:n_items) {
    item_residuals <- std_residuals[, j]
    item_outliers <- sum(abs(item_residuals) > outlier_threshold, na.rm = TRUE)
    item_responses <- sum(!is.na(item_residuals))
    item_outlier_rate <- 100 * item_outliers / item_responses
    
    cat(sprintf("  Item %d: %d outliers (%.1f%%)\n", 
                j, item_outliers, item_outlier_rate))
  }
  
  # Person-level residual analysis  
  person_outlier_counts <- rowSums(abs(std_residuals) > outlier_threshold, na.rm = TRUE)
  problem_persons <- sum(person_outlier_counts >= 3)
  
  cat("\nPerson-Level Residual Analysis:\n")
  cat("  Persons with ≥3 outlier responses:", problem_persons, "\n")
  
  # Residual plots
  if(require(ggplot2, quietly = TRUE)) {
    # Residual vs fitted plot
    fitted_values <- as.vector(expected_probs)
    residual_values <- as.vector(std_residuals)
    
    plot_data <- data.frame(
      Fitted = fitted_values,
      Residuals = residual_values
    ) %>% filter(!is.na(Fitted) & !is.na(Residuals))
    
    residual_plot <- ggplot(plot_data, aes(x = Fitted, y = Residuals)) +
      geom_point(alpha = 0.5, color = "blue") +
      geom_hline(yintercept = 0, color = "red", linetype = "dashed") +
      geom_hline(yintercept = c(-2.5, 2.5), color = "orange", linetype = "dotted") +
      labs(title = paste("Standardized Residuals vs Fitted -", data_name),
           x = "Fitted Probability", y = "Standardized Residuals") +
      theme_minimal()
    
    print(residual_plot)
    
    # Q-Q plot
    qq_plot <- ggplot(plot_data, aes(sample = Residuals)) +
      stat_qq(color = "blue", alpha = 0.6) +
      stat_qq_line(color = "red", linetype = "dashed") +
      labs(title = paste("Q-Q Plot of Residuals -", data_name),
           x = "Theoretical Quantiles", y = "Sample Quantiles") +
      theme_minimal()
    
    print(qq_plot)
  }
  
  # Overall residual assessment
  if(outlier_rate < 5) {
    residual_quality <- "Yaxşı"
  } else if(outlier_rate < 10) {
    residual_quality <- "Məqbul"
  } else {
    residual_quality <- "Problemli"
  }
  
  cat("\nÜmumi residual qiymətləndirməsi:", residual_quality, "\n\n")
  
  return(list(
    outlier_rate = outlier_rate,
    problem_persons = problem_persons,
    residual_quality = residual_quality,
    raw_residuals = raw_residuals,
    std_residuals = std_residuals
  ))
}

# Residual analysis for all scenarios
residual_results <- list()
for(i in 1:length(scenarios)) {
  residual_results[[names(scenarios)[i]]] <- 
    perform_residual_analysis(scenarios[[i]], names(scenarios)[i])
}

## 
## === COMPREHENSIVE MODEL ASSESSMENT SUMMARY ===
# Comprehensive assessment funksiyası
create_comprehensive_summary <- function() {
  
  # Collect all results
  summary_data <- data.frame(
    Ssenari = names(scenarios),
    
    # Dimensionality
    Eigenvalue_Ratio = sapply(names(scenarios), function(x) {
      if(x %in% names(dim_results) && !is.null(dim_results[[x]])) {
        round(dim_results[[x]]$lambda_ratio, 2)
      } else NA
    }),
    
    Dimensionality = sapply(names(scenarios), function(x) {
      if(x %in% names(dim_results) && !is.null(dim_results[[x]])) {
        dim_results[[x]]$assessment
      } else "N/A"
    }),
    
    # Local Independence
    Max_Q3 = sapply(names(scenarios), function(x) {
      if(x %in% names(q3_results)) {
        round(max(q3_results[[x]]$q3_values), 3)
      } else NA
    }),
    
    Local_Independence = sapply(names(scenarios), function(x) {
      if(x %in% names(q3_results)) {
        q3_results[[x]]$assessment
      } else "N/A"
    }),
    
    # Monotonicity
    Monotonicity = sapply(names(scenarios), function(x) {
      if(x %in% names(mokken_results)) {
        mokken_results[[x]]$quality
      } else "N/A"
    }),
    
    # Model Fit  
    Model_Fit = sapply(names(scenarios), function(x) {
      if(x %in% names(fit_results)) {
        if("person_fit_quality" %in% names(fit_results[[x]])) {
          fit_results[[x]]$person_fit_quality
        } else {
          fit_results[[x]]$fit_quality
        }
      } else "N/A"
    }),
    
    # Residuals
    Residual_Quality = sapply(names(scenarios), function(x) {
      if(x %in% names(residual_results)) {
        residual_results[[x]]$residual_quality
      } else "N/A"
    })
  )
  
  return(summary_data)
}

# Overall assessment for each scenario
cat("\n=== OVERALL SCENARIO ASSESSMENTS ===\n\n")
## 
## === OVERALL SCENARIO ASSESSMENTS ===
assess_scenario <- function(scenario_name, summary_row) {
  cat("SSENARI:", toupper(scenario_name), "\n")
  
  # Count positive assessments
  positive_indicators <- 0
  total_indicators <- 0
  
  issues <- c()
  
  # Dimensionality
  if(!is.na(summary_row$Eigenvalue_Ratio)) {
    total_indicators <- total_indicators + 1
    if(summary_row$Eigenvalue_Ratio >= 2) {
      positive_indicators <- positive_indicators + 1
    } else {
      issues <- c(issues, "Multidimensionality")
    }
  }
  
  # Local Independence  
  if(!is.na(summary_row$Max_Q3)) {
    total_indicators <- total_indicators + 1
    if(summary_row$Max_Q3 <= 0.20) {
      positive_indicators <- positive_indicators + 1
    } else {
      issues <- c(issues, "Local Dependence")
    }
  }
  
  # Quality categories
  quality_scores <- 0
  if(summary_row$Model_Fit %in% c("Yaxşı", "Məqbul")) quality_scores <- quality_scores + 1
  if(summary_row$Residual_Quality %in% c("Yaxşı", "Məqbul")) quality_scores <- quality_scores + 1
  
  # Overall assessment
  if(length(issues) == 0 && quality_scores >= 1) {
    overall <- "İdeal IRT Data - Bütün fərziyyələr təmin olunur"
  } else if(length(issues) <= 1 && quality_scores >= 1) {
    overall <- "Yaxşı IRT Data - Kiçik məsələlər var"
  } else if(length(issues) <= 2) {
    overall <- "Problemli IRT Data - Müdaxilə lazımdır"
  } else {
    overall <- "IRT üçün Uyğun Deyil - Fundamental dəyişikliklər lazım"
  }
  
  cat("Əsas məsələlər:", ifelse(length(issues) == 0, "Yoxdur", paste(issues, collapse = ", ")), "\n")
  cat("Ümumi qiymətləndirmə:", overall, "\n")
  
  # Recommendations
  cat("Tövsiyələr:\n")
  if(length(issues) == 0) {
    cat("  • Data IRT üçün idealdır, modellə davam edin\n")
  } else {
    if("Multidimensionality" %in% issues) {
      cat("  • MIRT (çoxölçülü IRT) modelləri nəzərdən keçirin\n")
      cat("  • Subdimensions üçün ayrı analizlər aparın\n")
    }
    if("Local Dependence" %in% issues) {
      cat("  • Testlet modelləri istifadə edin\n")
      cat("  • Problematik item pairləri nəzərdən keçirin\n")
    }
    if(summary_row$Model_Fit == "Problemli") {
      cat("  • Item content və quality-ni yoxlayın\n")
      cat("  • Test instruction və administration yoxlayın\n")
    }
  }
  cat("\n")
}

# Assess each scenario
for(i in 1:nrow(comprehensive_summary)) {
  assess_scenario(comprehensive_summary$Ssenari[i], comprehensive_summary[i, ])
}
